    "LR measures the relationship between the response (dependent) variable and one or more explanatory (independent) variables for a given dataset that indicates the significance and strength of the impact of the explanatory variables on the response variable.",
    "The response variable is a class label that we are trying to predict.",
    "However, the explanatory variables are the features or attributes used to predict the class label.",
    "The output of LR is the probability that given input points belong to a certain class.",
    "Typically, LR estimates probabilities using the logistic function, also known as the sigmoid function, which is given in Eq."
